quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  8,41,"Know that, whatever booty you take, the fifth of it is God's, and the Messenger's, and the near kinsman's, and the orphans', and for the needy, and the traveller, if you believe in God and that We sent down upon Our servant on the day of salvation,. the day the two hosts encountered; and God is powerful over everything"
  8,42,"when you were on the nearer bank, and they were on the farther bank, and the cavalcade was below you; and had you made tryst together, you would have surely failed the tryst; but that God might determine a matter that was done, that whosoever perished might perish by a clear sign, and by a clear sign he might live who lived; and surely God is All-hearing, All-knowing"
  8,43,"When God showed thee them in thy dream as few; and had He shown them as many you would have lost heart, and quarrelled about the matter; but God saved; He knows the thoughts in the breasts"
  8,44,"When God showed you them in your eyes as few, when you encountered, and made you few in their eyes, that God might determine a matter that was done; and unto God all matters are returned"
  8,45,"O believers, whensoever you encounter a host, then stand firm, and remember God frequently; haply so you will prosper"
  8,46,"And obey God, and His Messenger, and do not quarrel together, and so lose heart, and your power depart; and be patient; surely God is with the patient"
  8,47,"Be not as those who went forth from their habitations swaggering boastfully to show off to men, and barring from God's way; and God encompasses the things they do"
  8,48,"And when Satan decked out their deeds fair to them, and said, 'Today no man shall overcome you, for I shall be your neighbour.' But when the two hosts sighted each other, he withdrew upon his heels, saying, 'I am quit of you; for I see what you do not see. I fear God; and God is terrible in retribution"
  8,49,"When the hypocrites, and those in whose hearts was sickness, said, 'Their religion has deluded them'; but whosoever puts his trust in God, surely God is All-mighty, All-wise"
  8,50,"If thou couldst only see when the angels take the unbelievers, beating their faces and their backs: 'Taste the chastisement of the burning"
  8,51,"that, for what your hands have forwarded, and for that God is never unjust unto His servants"
  8,52,"Like Pharaoh's folk, and the people before him, who disbelieved in God's signs; God seized them because of their sins; God is strong, terrible in retribution"
  8,53,"That is because God would never change His favour that He conferred on a people until they changed what was within themselves; and that God is All-hearing, All-knowing"
  8,54,"Like Pharaoh's folk, and the people before him, who cried lies to the signs of their Lord, so We destroyed them because of their sins, and We drowned the folk of Pharaoh; and all were evildoers"
  8,55,"Surely the worst of beasts in God's sight are the unbelievers, who will not believe"
  8,56,"those of them with whom thou hast made compact then they break their compact every time, not being godfearing"
  8,57,"So, if thou comest upon them anywhere in the war, deal with them in such wise as to scatter the ones behind them; haply they will remember"
  8,58,"And if thou fearest treachery any way at the hands of a people, dissolve it with them equally; surely God loves not the treacherous"
  8,59,And thou art not to suppose that they who disbelieve have outstripped Me; they cannot frustrate My will
  8,60,"Make ready for them whatever force and strings of horses you can, to terrify thereby the enemy of God and your enemy, and others besides them that you know not; God knows them. And whatsoever you expend in the way of God shall be repaid you in full; you will not be wronged"